<tmc-service-inc>
<pub id="RM0251U">
<servcat id="42">
<name>BODY ELECTRICAL</name>
<section id="1001I_S001E" variety="S001E">
<name>DOOR LOCK</name>
<ttl id="1001I_S001E_73040_T00DI" variety="T00DI">
<name>KEY REMINDER WARNING SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM0000011G200EX" category="D" type-id="3001B" name-id="DL04C-12" from="200601">
<name>HOW TO PROCEED WITH TROUBLESHOOTING</name>
<subpara id="RM0000011G200EX_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___00008PF00000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Use the following procedures to troubleshoot the key reminder warning system.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>The intelligent tester should be used in steps 3 and 5.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
<descript-diag>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>VEHICLE BROUGHT TO WORKSHOP</testtitle>
<results>
<result-ci-down>NEXT</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>INSPECT BATTERY VOLTAGE</testtitle>
<test1>
<ptxt>Measure the battery voltage.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard voltage</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>10 to 14 V</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the voltage is below 10 V, recharge or replace the battery before proceeding to the next step.</ptxt>
</test1>
<results>
<result-ci-down>NEXT</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>INSPECT COMMUNICATION FUNCTION OF CAN COMMUNICATION SYSTEM (CAN)</testtitle>
<test1>
<ptxt>Use the intelligent tester to check if the CAN communication system (CAN) is functioning normally.</ptxt>
<test2>
<ptxt>(ECU connected, communication line malfunctioning) If no code is output, proceed to A.</ptxt>
</test2>
<test2>
<ptxt>(ECU connected, communication line malfunctioning) If any code is output, proceed to B.</ptxt>
</test2>
</test1>
<results>
<result>B</result>
<action-ci-right>GO TO CAN COMMUNICATION SYSTEM</action-ci-right>
<result-ci-down>A</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>PROBLEM SYMPTOMS TABLE</testtitle>
<test1>
<ptxt>If the fault is not listed in the problem symptoms table, proceed to A.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>If the fault is listed in the problem symptoms table, proceed to B.</ptxt>
</test1>
<results>
<result>B</result>
<action-ci-right>Go to step 6</action-ci-right>
<result-ci-down>A</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>OVERALL ANALYSIS AND TROUBLESHOOTING</testtitle>
<test1>
<ptxt>Inspection with the intelligent tester (DATA LIST)</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>TERMINALS OF ECU (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000011G400EX"/>)</ptxt>
</test1>
<results>
<result-ci-down>NEXT</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE</testtitle>
<results>
<result-ci-down>NEXT</result-ci-down>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
<descript-testgroup>
<testtitle>CONFIRMATION TEST</testtitle>
<results>
<result-ci-down>NEXT</result-ci-down>
<action-ci-fin>END</action-ci-fin>
</results>
</descript-testgroup>
</descript-diag>
</content5>
</subpara>
</para>
</ttl>
</section>
</servcat>
</pub>
